<section id="subFs">
<title>subFs</title>
<para>Sub-format style, subFs - allows extra metadata, like URL for example, to be added in concert
with the <olink targetdoc="../attributes/fs.xml" targetptr="fs"><code>fs</code></olink> attribute. </para>

<para><emphasis>Value description:</emphasis> The subFs attribute is used to specify the HTML
        attributes to use along with the HTML element declared in the <olink
            targetdoc="../attributes/fs.xml" targetptr="fs"><code>fs</code></olink> attribute. It is
        a list of name/value pairs. Each pair is separated from the next with a backslash (\). The
        name and the value of a pair are separated with a comma (,). Both literal backslash and
        comma characters are escaped with a backslash prefix.
        <!-- was
 The subFs <glossterm>must</glossterm> only be used to carry attribute name/value
comma-delimited pairs for attributes that are valid for the HTML element identified by the
accompanied <olink targetdoc="../attributes/fs.xml" targetptr="fs"><code>fs</code></olink> attribute.
-->
    </para>
<!-- this is now redundant
<para>Example:<code> fs:fs="img" fs:subFs="src,smileface.png"</code>. </para>-->
<para><emphasis>Default value:</emphasis> undefined.</para>
<para><emphasis>Used in:</emphasis>
<olink targetdoc="../elements/structural/file.xml" targetptr="file"
><code>&lt;file&gt;</code></olink>, <!--<olink targetdoc="../elements/structural/skeleton.xml"
targetptr="skeleton"><code>&lt;skeleton&gt;</code></olink>, [does not make sense for skeleton IMHO]-->
<olink targetdoc="../elements/structural/unit.xml" targetptr="unit"
><code>&lt;unit&gt;</code></olink>,





 <olink
targetdoc="../elements/structural/note.xml" targetptr="note"><code>&lt;note&gt;</code></olink>, <!---
<olink targetdoc="../elements/candidates/match.xml"
targetptr="match"><code>&lt;match&gt;</code></olink>, [I'd consider having it on this module as well]-->





<olink
targetdoc="../elements/structural/source.xml" targetptr="source"
><code>&lt;source&gt;</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../elements/structural/target.xml"
targetptr="target"><code>&lt;target&gt;</code></olink>,






<olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/sc.xml"
targetptr="sc"><code>&lt;sc&gt;</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/ec.xml"
targetptr="ec"><code>&lt;ec&gt;</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/ph.xml"
targetptr="ph"><code>&lt;ph&gt;</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/pc.xml"
targetptr="pc"><code>&lt;pc&gt;</code></olink>, <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/mrk.xml"
targetptr="mrk"><code>&lt;mrk&gt;</code></olink>, and <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/sm.xml"
targetptr="sm"><code>&lt;sm&gt;</code></olink>. </para>
<warning><para>The <link linkend="subFs"><code>subFs</code></link> attribute is not intended to facilitate <firstterm>Merging</firstterm> back into the original format. </para></warning>

<itemizedlist>
<title>Constraints</title>
<listitem><para>Commas (<code>,</code>) and backslashes (<code>\</code>) in the value parts of the <link linkend="subFs"><code>subFs</code></link> <glossterm>must</glossterm> be escaped with a
backslash (<code>\</code>).</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>If the attribute <link  linkend="subFs"><code>subFs</code></link> is used, the attribute <olink
targetdoc="../attributes/fs.xml" targetptr="fs"><code>fs</code></olink>
<glossterm>must</glossterm> be specified as well.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para>The <link linkend="subFs"><code>subFs</code></link> <glossterm>must</glossterm> only be used with <olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/ec.xml"
targetptr="ec"><code>&lt;ec&gt;</code></olink> in cases where the <code>isolated</code> attribute is set to 'yes'.</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<itemizedlist>
<title>Processing Requirements</title>
<listitem>
<para><firstterm>Writers</firstterm> updating the attribute <olink
targetdoc="fs.xml" targetptr="fs"><code>fs</code></olink> <glossterm>must</glossterm> also update or delete <link  linkend="subFs"><code>subFs</code></link>.</para>
</listitem>


</itemizedlist>
